						               													<description>Repulse is a strategic card game consisting of 110 cards in 3 categories.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Is a good defense perhaps better than an attack? Can it be that you set up the tactic that leads to the goal? Are you ready?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Regardless of the game variant, it&amp;rsquo;s about being the first to defeat another army, so there are no more cards in front of an opponent. Always keep in mind that a wrong move may allow another player to win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn: Pick up two cards from the middle of the pile (or your own - depending on the game variant). You can attack with the face-up cards you face. You can play some action cards in your hand at any time (during an attack or while another player's turn takes place), others only when it's your turn. Once you've completed your attacks, you can reveal up to two face-down cards (or just one or none at all) and put them forward and replace them with hand cards. A maximum of 3 cards may be revealed and two cards face down. Think good of your strategy, because if you make too many attacks, you may not be able to defend yourself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If an attack is made and it succeeds by higher value, both cards are placed on the open stack in the middle. If the attacker's army card value is lower than the defending card, the attack failed and the attack card is placed on the open stack in the middle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
